input_text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to see page likes on facebook?
input_text.Response A: Sure, you can do this from the facebook app or website.  If you’re using the app, you can click on the “Like” button next to any post, and you’ll see the number of people who have liked the post.  If you’re using the website, you can click on the “Like” button next to any post, and you’ll see the number of people who have liked the post, as well as the number of people who have shared the post.  You can also click on the “Like” button next to your own profile picture, and you’ll see the number of people who have liked your profile picture.  You can also click on the “Like” button next to a page, and you’ll see the number of people who have liked the page.
input_text.Response B: Sure! I’m happy to help you. If you go to your profile page and click on the “Like” button, you can see the people who like your page.

label_annotations.feedback: Although Response A gave some very helpful information, it was much more than what was asked and was very redundant and could be confusing to a person asking the question. Response B was much more direct and in line with the request.
